<subsection>
<title>Numerical Practice</title>

	
	<exploration xml:id="psa_rot-alpha5">
		<title>Moment of Inertia</title>
		<statement><p></p>
			<p>
				Which of the following statements concerning the moment of inertia <em>I</em> are false?
			</p>
			<p>
				<ol marker="A">
				  <li><em>I</em> may be expressed in units of <m>\mathrm{~kg m^2}</m></li>
				  <li><em>I</em> depends on the angular acceleration of the object as it rotates</li>
				  <li><em>I</em> depends on the location of the rotation axis relative to the particles that make up the object.</li>
				  <li><em>I</em> depends on the orientation of the rotation axis relative to the particles that make up the object.</li>
				</ol>
			  </p>
		</statement>
		<answer>
			<p>
				B.
			</p>
		</answer>
	</exploration>

